        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 18 at 4:27PM EDT until June 18 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles northwest
of Sharon, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Trained spotters and doppler radar reported.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Hermitage, Sharon, Sharpsville, Greenville, Farrell, New
Wilmington, Mercer, Pulaski, New Bedford, West Middlesex, Plain
Grove Township, Clark, Wheatland, Fredonia, Jackson Center,
Volant, Sheakleyville and Maurice K Goddard State Park.

A wind gust of 58 mph was reported at the Youngstown Warren Regional
Airport in Trumbull county Ohio.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm has produced damaging winds.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
